Privacy Policy for Squishy Stack

Effective Date: 14/08/2024

Welcome to Squishy Stack, a hyper-casual mobile game developed by Loconut Games. Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and share information about you when you use our app, "Squishy Stack," available on the Google Play Store.

1. Information We Collect
When you use Squishy Stack, we may collect the following types of information:

Personal Information: We do not collect any personally identifiable information directly through the app. However, if you sign in using Google Play Services, we may collect basic profile information (such as your Google username, avatar, and email) associated with your Google account.

Leaderboard Data: To participate in the global leaderboard, we collect your gameplay scores and associate them with your Google Play account. This data is used to display your ranking on the leaderboard.

Device Information: We may collect information about the device you are using, such as the device model, operating system version, unique device identifiers, and mobile network information.

Usage Data: We may collect information about how you interact with the game, such as the levels you complete, your high scores, and other gameplay statistics.

2. How We Use the Information
The information we collect is used to:

Provide and Improve the Game: We use the collected data to operate, maintain, and enhance Squishy Stack, including tracking your progress, managing leaderboards, and ensuring a smooth gaming experience.

Leaderboard and Social Features: If you choose to participate in leaderboards, your scores and Google Play profile information will be displayed to other players.

Analytics and Performance Monitoring: We may use the data to analyze how players interact with the game, which helps us improve game features and user experience.

3. How We Share Your Information
Loconut Games does not share your personal information with third parties, except in the following circumstances:

Google Play Services: As our game integrates with Google Play Services, your data (such as leaderboard scores and Google Play profile information) may be shared with Google according to their privacy policy.

Legal Requirements: We may disclose your information if required to do so by law or in response to valid requests by public authorities (e.g., a court or government agency).

4. Data Security
We take reasonable measures to protect the information we collect from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction. However, no security measures are entirely foolproof, and we cannot guarantee the absolute security of your information.

5. Childrenâ€™s Privacy
Squishy Stack is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you believe that we have inadvertently collected such information, please contact us so that we can promptly delete it.

6. Your Choices
Opt-Out of Leaderboards: If you do not wish to participate in the leaderboards, you can choose not to sign in to Google Play Services or disable the leaderboard feature within the game settings.

Data Deletion: If you wish to delete your data, including leaderboard scores and associated profile information, please refer to the contact details provided in the app store listing for Squishy Stack to request data deletion.

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. If we make any changes, we will notify you by updating the "Effective Date" at the top of this policy. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically to stay informed about how we are protecting your information.

8. Contact Us
For any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please refer to the contact details provided in the app store listing for Squishy Stack.

By using Squishy Stack, you agree to the collection and use of your information as described in this Privacy Policy.
